{{Infobox scientist | name = Janet Liebman Jacobs | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = 1948 <!--{{birth date |YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | birth_place = | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)--> | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = American | fields = Sociology, [[Sociology of Religion]], Trauma in Society, [[Gender studies|Gender Analysis]] | workplaces = University of Colorado | patrons = | education = BS, MPA, PhD | alma_mater = University of Colorado | thesis_title = <!--(or | thesis1_title = and | thesis2_title = )--> | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = <!--(or | thesis1_year = and | thesis2_year = )--> | doctoral_advisor = <!--(or | doctoral_advisors = )--> | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = Interdisciplinary research in gender, religion and trauma studies | influences = | influenced = | awards = Distinguished book award from the Society for the Scientific Study of Religion, Hazel Barnes Prize, Outstanding Book Award in 2017 from the [[American Sociological Association]] | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = }}
'''Janet Liebman Jacobs''' (born 1948) is an American sociologist specializing in gender and religion. Jacobs' research focuses on women, religion, ethnicity, genocide and the social psychology of gender. She has authored seven books, including ''Hidden Heritage: The Legacy of the Crypto-Jews'',<ref name=hidden>{{cite book|last1=Jacobs|first1=Janet|title=Hidden Heritage: The Legacy of the Crypto-Jews|date=2002|publisher=University of California Press|url=http://www.ucpress.edu/book.php?isbn=9780520235175}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ward|first1=Seth|title=Hidden Heritage, the Legacy of the Crypto-Jews (review)|url=http://muse.jhu.edu/article/188365|website=Muse|publisher=muse.jhu.edu|accessdate=14 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Neulander|first1=Judith S|title=Reviewed Work: Hidden Heritage: The Legacy of the Crypto-Jews by Janet Liebman Jacobs|jstor=1500440|publisher=Western Folklore}}</ref><ref name="Science 2.0">{{cite web|last1=Entine|first1=Jon|title=The 'Jew' In All Of Us|url=http://www.science20.com/jon_entine_contrarian/jew_all_us-90698|website=Science 2.0|publisher=Science 2.0|accessdate=2 April 2015}}</ref> for which she won the Distinguished Book Award from the Society for the Scientific Study of Religion,<ref name="University of Colorado2">{{cite web|title=Faculty Awards |url=https://sociology.colorado.edu/people/faculty-awards |website=Department of Sociology |publisher=University of Colorado |accessdate=2 April 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150404160625/https://sociology.colorado.edu/people/faculty-awards |archivedate= 4 April 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sssrweb.org/PastWinners.cfm#Award1 |title=Past Award Winners |website=Society for the Scientific Study of Religion |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5nkN0WHJc?url=http://www.sssrweb.org/PastWinners.cfm |archivedate=2010-02-23 |df= }}</ref> ''Memorializing the Holocaust: Gender, Genocide and Collective Memory'',<ref name=memorializing>{{cite book|last1=Jacobs|first1=Janet|title=Memorializing the Holocaust: Gender, Genocide and Collective Memory|date=2010|publisher=I.B. Tauris|url=http://www.ibtauris.com/Books/Humanities/History/History%20specific%20events%20%20topics/Genocide%20%20ethnic%20cleansing/The%20Holocaust/Memorializing%20the%20Holocaust%20Gender%20Genocide%20and%20Collective%20Memory.aspx?menuitem=%7B6D00AE6F-976D-4418-ACF0-B75CB610346A%7D}}</ref> and The Holocaust Across Generations: Trauma and its Inheritance Among Descendents of Survivors, for which she won the 2017 Outstanding Book Award from the [[American Sociological Association]].<ref name="NYU 2017">{{cite web|title=The Holocaust Across Generations Trauma and its Inheritance Among Descendants of Survivors|url=https://nyupress.org/books/9781479839292/|website=NYU Press|publisher=NYU Press|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref>
Jacobs is currently Professor of Sociology<ref name=uc>{{cite web|url=https://sociology.colorado.edu/people/jacobs-janet |title=Janet Jacobs |website=Department of Sociology |publisher=University of Colorado Boulder |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216083940/http://sociology.colorado.edu/people/jacobs-janet |archivedate=2015-02-16 |df= }}</ref> and of Women and Gender Studies<ref name=wgst>{{cite web|url=http://wgst.colorado.edu/faculty/jacobs|title=Janet Jacobs|website=Women and Gender Studies |publisher=University of Colorado Boulder}}</ref> at the [[University of Colorado]], and she directs the University of Colorado Honors Program. She received her PhD from the University of Colorado in 1985.<ref name="auto4">{{cite web|url=http://www.colorado.edu/honors/janetjacobs|title=Janet Jacobs|website=Honors Program|publisher=University of Colorado Boulder}}</ref>
==Career== Jacobs earned a [[Bachelor of Science|BS]] in journalism in 1970, a [[Master of Public Administration]] degree in 1977, and a PhD in sociology at the University of Colorado in 1985. Jacobs is a [[tenure]]d full professor in the Department of Sociology and professor of Women's Studies at the University of Colorado, [[Boulder, Colorado|Boulder]].<ref name=uc/> She served as the director of the Women's Studies Program at this institution in 1987-1988 and again during 1997-2000;<ref name=wgst/> she also served as director of the Farrand Academic Program from 2005-2011. Since 2014 Jacobs has directed the University of Colorado College of Arts and Sciences Honors Program. Jacobs chaired the committee and has supervised research for graduates of the University of Colorado, Boulder and has received Teaching Excellence Awards from the University of Colorado in 1985, 1992 and 2001.<ref>{{cite web|title=Teaching Excellence Awards|url=https://www.colorado.edu/bfa/excellence-awards/bfa-excellence-awards-archives/teaching-excellence-awards|website=Boulder Faculty Assembly|publisher=University of Colorado Boulder|accessdate=13 October 2017}}</ref>
