'''Karen Elizabeth Boyle''' (born 22 October 1972),<ref name=Congress>{{cite web|title=Boyle, Karen, 1972– |url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/nr2004036282.html |publisher=Library of Congress|accessdate= 23 October 2015| quote = (Karen Elizabeth Boyle; b. Oct. 22, 1972) }}</ref> is Professor of Feminist Media Studies at the [[University of Strathclyde]], previously she was professor of Feminist Studies at the [[University of Stirling]],<ref>{{Citation | last1 = Carter | first1 = Cynthia | last2 = Steiner | first2 = Linda | last3 = McLaughlin | first3 = Lisa | author-link1 = Cynthia Carter | author-link2 = Linda Steiner | contribution = Contributors | editor-last1 = Carter | editor-first1 = Cynthia | editor-last2 = Steiner | editor-first2 = Linda | editor-last3 = McLaughlin | editor-first3 = Lisa | editor-link1 = Cynthia Carter | editor-link2 = Linda Steiner | title = The Routledge companion to media & gender | publisher = Routledge | page = xiii | location = London New York | year = 2015 | isbn = 9781138849129 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref> and before that was a lecturer in film and television studies at the [[University of Glasgow]]. She has published a number of articles on feminism, violence and pornography.<ref>{{Citation | last = Allen | first = Michael | contribution = Contributors | editor-last = Allen | editor-first = Michael | title = Reading CSI crime TV under the microscope | page = ix | publisher = I.B. Tauris | location = London New York | year = 2007 | isbn = 9781845114282 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref>

Boyle sits on the editorial boards of both ''[[Feminist Media Studies]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Editorial board: Feminist Media Studies|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?show=editorialBoard&journalCode=rfms20|publisher=[[Taylor and Francis]]|accessdate= 23 October 2015}}</ref> and ''[[Sexualization, Media, and Society]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Editorial board: Sexualization, Media, and Society|url=https://uk.sagepub.com/en-gb/eur/sexualization-media-society/journal202355#editorial-board|publisher=[[Sage Publications|Sage]]|accessdate= 23 October 2015}}</ref>

